# Hidden Markov Models

---

## Structure

```python
class HMM:
    def __init__(self, num_states, num_observations):
        # Initial state distribution
        self.pi = torch.randn(num_states)
        
        # Transition matrix A[i,j] = P(s_t=j | s_{t-1}=i)
        self.A = torch.randn(num_states, num_states)
        
        # Emission matrix B[j,k] = P(o_t=k | s_t=j)
        self.B = torch.randn(num_states, num_observations)
    
    def forward(self, observations):
        # Forward algorithm to compute P(o_1,...,o_T)
        alpha = self.pi * self.B[:, observations[0]]
        for obs in observations[1:]:
            alpha = (alpha @ self.A) * self.B[:, obs]
        return alpha.sum()
```

---

## Three Problems

| Problem | Algorithm |
|---------|-----------|
| **Likelihood** | Forward algorithm |
| **Decoding** | Viterbi algorithm |
| **Learning** | Baum-Welch (EM) |